messages.subject: Re: Sarasota trip
messages.msgSnippet: Sam, The one in Sarasota is the first weekend of March (Thursday - Sunday), on the grounds of the Ringling Museum, right on Hwy. 41.  There s another one in
messages.messageBody:
Sam,

The one in Sarasota is the first weekend of March (Thursday - Sunday), on the
grounds of the Ringling Museum, right on Hwy. 41. There's another one in
Largo (near St. Pete) in April, and it runs for like 5 or 6 weekends. We've
never been to that one, but have heard it's really good. The Sarasota one is
our absolute favorite thing to do - we love it!!!

Here's a site with a listing of Renaissance Faires all over the country - and
I have a ton more sites, if you'd like them; just let me know and I'll share
:)

Maybe we'll meet in Sarasota next year!

Linda in FL :)

messages.subject: Re: Sarasota trip
messages.msgSnippet: Just a little further south (less than 30 minutes) is Venice Beach - famous for shark s teeth!  You can just walk along the beach and practically scoop them
messages.messageBody:
Just a little further south (less than 30 minutes) is Venice Beach - famous
for shark's teeth! You can just walk along the beach and practically scoop
them up. We haven't been in a few years (We live in Cape Coral, a little
further south yet), but I hear that it's still like that.

Mote Marine is also in Sarasota, a great marine research facility. Again,
it's been years since we've been, but the public school kids do field trips
there, and I'm sure it would be possible to set something up - a tour, or
maybe they're open to the public. If you can't find anything about it, let
me know and I'll see what I can do from this end.

Now you've got me wanting to make a drive up to Sarasota! We go every March
to the Rennaisance Faire, and occasionally to St. Armand's Key (which is a
wonderful little "roundabout", full of exclusive shops and restaurants, and
the best place to walk around and windowshop!), but it's been awhile...hmmm,
let me know when you're going to be there, Sandy, and maybe we could meet
somewhere?

Let me know if I can help any more from here :)


Linda in FL :)
